{
  "name": "al-translation-requirements",
  "displayName": "AL Translation Requirements",
  "description": "Enforce required translation files and manage equivalent languages in AL extensions",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "publisher": "gerardo-renteria",
  "icon": "icon.png",
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "https://github.com/gdrgdev/Blog/tree/main/GDRGDev_VSCALTranslationRequirements"
  },
  "engines": {
    "vscode": "^1.85.0"
  },
  "categories": [
    "Programming Languages"
  ],
  "keywords": [
    "AL",
    "Business Central",
    "Translation",
    "XLIFF",
    "Localization"
  ],
  "activationEvents": [
    "workspaceContains:**/app.json"
  ],
  "main": "./out/extension.js",
  "contributes": {
    "commands": [
      {
        "command": "alTranslationRequirements.validate",
        "title": "AL Translation Requirements: Validate"
      },
      {
        "command": "alTranslationRequirements.syncEquivalents",
        "title": "AL Translation Requirements: Sync Equivalents"
      }
    ],
    "configuration": {
      "title": "AL Translation Requirements",
      "properties": {
        "alTranslationRequirements.required": {
          "type": "array",
          "default": [],
          "scope": "resource",
          "description": "Required language codes (e.g., ['es-ES', 'fr-FR'])",
          "items": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        "alTranslationRequirements.equivalents": {
          "type": "array",
          "default": [],
          "scope": "resource",
          "markdownDescription": "**Equivalent language mappings** - Creates copies of translation files with different language codes.\n\n**How to use:**\n1. Click **\"Edit in settings.json\"** below\n2. Add your mappings like this example:\n```json\n\"alTranslationRequirements.equivalents\": [\n  {\n    \"base\": \"es-ES\",\n    \"equivalent\": \"es-MX\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"base\": \"fr-FR\",\n    \"equivalent\": \"fr-CA\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\n**What it does:** Copies `es-ES.xlf` → `es-MX.xlf` (and updates the target language).\n\n**Common use cases:**\n- Spanish variants: `es-ES` → `es-MX`, `es-ES` → `es-AR`\n- French variants: `fr-FR` → `fr-CA`, `fr-FR` → `fr-BE`\n- English variants: `en-US` → `en-GB`, `en-US` → `en-AU`",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "base": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "Source language code (must exist in Required list)",
                "examples": ["es-ES", "fr-FR", "en-US"]
              },
              "equivalent": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "Target language code (will be created from base)",
                "examples": ["es-MX", "fr-CA", "en-GB"]
              }
            },
            "required": ["base", "equivalent"]
          }
        },
        "alTranslationRequirements.decoration.backgroundColor": {
          "type": "string",
          "default": "#F0D269",
          "scope": "resource",
          "description": "Background color for trans-units with missing or empty target (hex format)"
        },
        "alTranslationRequirements.decoration.enabled": {
          "type": "boolean",
          "default": true,
          "scope": "resource",
          "description": "Enable/disable decoration for missing translations"
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "scripts": {
    "vscode:prepublish": "npm run compile",
    "compile": "tsc -p ./",
    "watch": "tsc -watch -p ./"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@types/node": "^20.x",
    "@types/vscode": "^1.85.0",
    "typescript": "^5.3.0"
  }
}
